  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency Shelter and Non-food Item (NFI) Assistance to Internally Displaced Persons (IDPs) and Host Communities in the Provinces of Kouritenga and Boulgou in the Center-East Region</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Given the growing number of internally displaced persons (IDPs) in the Centre-East region of Burkina Faso, which is considered an underfunded area regarding humanitarian assistance, IOM is proposing a targeted intervention to provide emergency shelter assistance and non-food item kits to IDPs and host community households in the communes most affected by internal displacement, namely Kouritenga and Boulgou.</narrative>
  </description>
